        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(control-ui): improve session key display for direct chats with long identifiers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen the Control Dashboard session list displays direct (non-group) sessions without a resolved agent identity or label, it falls back to showing the full raw session key — including long identifiers like `ou_67075ec667cac0a7feae2c5094fd27b2`. This PR addresses the issue by:\n\n1. Truncating long identifiers (>20 chars) in the session key display fallback\n2. Wiring the shared `resolveSessionDisplayName` helper into the Sessions table key cell and details panel title (ClawSweeper P2)\n\nWhat is intentionally out of scope:\n- Resolving `binding.comment` at session recording time (requires config access not available in the message context)\n- Persisting derived display names as session metadata (removed after ClawSweeper P2 feedback)\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `ui/src/ui/session-display.ts` | +10/-1 — add `shortenDirectIdentifier()` to truncate long IDs to `abc...wxyz` format |\n| `ui/src/ui/session-display.test.ts` | +111 — 16 new tests for `parseSessionKey()` and `resolveSessionDisplayName()` |\n| `ui/src/ui/views/sessions.ts` | +4/-3 — wire `resolveSessionDisplayName()` into key cell fallback and details title |\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** Long direct-chat identifiers are truncated in the Sessions table and detail panel fallback display\n- **Real environment tested:** Local checkout, vitest unit tests\n- **Exact commands run after patch:**\n  - `cd ui && pnpm vitest run src/ui/session-display.test.ts` — 16/16 passed\n  - `pnpm format:check` — 0 issues\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n  - `parseSessionKey(\"agent:main:feishu:direct:ou_67075ec667cac0a7feae2c5094fd27b2\")` returns `Feishu · ou_6707...27b2` (not the full 34-char ID)\n  - `resolveSessionDisplayName(key, row)` returns `Feishu · ou_6707...27b2` when no label/displayName/identity is available\n- **What was not tested:** Live Control Dashboard rendering (the helpers are pure functions verified by vitest; visual verification could use a real dashboard or `@openclaw-mantis`)\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `cd ui && pnpm vitest run src/ui/session-display.test.ts` — 16/16\n- `pnpm format:check` — clean\n\nTest coverage:\n- `parseSessionKey`: main, subagent, cron, direct, group, legacy, unknown formats\n- `parseSessionKey`: long identifiers truncated, short identifiers preserved\n- `resolveSessionDisplayName`: label precedence, displayName fallback, no-data fallback\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? Yes — direct session fallback names are truncated for readability.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? No.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? No.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area? Low — changes are in display-only helper functions and the sessions table renderer.\n\n## Addresses ClawSweeper findings\n\n- [P2] Fixed: sessions table key cell and details title now use `resolveSessionDisplayName()` for fallback display\n- [P2] Fixed: removed the persisted `displayName` write from session metadata (no stale label risk)\n- [P3] Fixed: removed `.cursor/issue-fix` scratch files from the PR\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-61213-session-display-id",
